WEBVTT

00:05.422 --> 00:07.583
[CROWD CHATTERING INSIDE]

00:10.803 --> 00:12.339
[DOOR OPENS]

00:14.098 --> 00:15.634
[DOOR CLOSES]

00:20.437 --> 00:21.517
Clark...

00:21.689 --> 00:23.896
...you shouldn't have.

00:24.817 --> 00:27.479
Uh, Clark's sorry he couldn't make it.
He and Bart are off—

00:27.653 --> 00:30.645
Yeah. Dealing with a crisis in Keystone.

00:30.823 --> 00:32.859
I know. Ha, ha.

00:34.243 --> 00:35.779
Come on, let's, uh, see what you got.

00:35.953 --> 00:37.443
[CH UCKLES]

00:40.457 --> 00:42.072
Oh. Ha, ha.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.370
Wow.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.126
I haven't seen this in ages.

00:53.137 --> 00:54.593
You okay?

00:56.724 --> 00:58.180
Yeah.

00:59.977 --> 01:03.310
Birthdays just make me a little reﬂective.

01:03.981 --> 01:07.144
What do you say we get you out
of your head and into the party, huh?

01:07.776 --> 01:08.811
-Come on.
-Hmm.

01:08.986 --> 01:10.772
[CROWD CHATTERING]

01:10.946 --> 01:12.982
[DANCE MUSIC
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

01:13.157 --> 01:15.614
See, case in point.

01:15.784 --> 01:17.490
That was supposed to be my life.

01:17.661 --> 01:18.650
[LAUGHS]

01:18.829 --> 01:20.160
CHLOE:
Ollie, when did this happen?

01:20.330 --> 01:23.663
One day, I'm on the fast track
for my dream career as the intrepid reporter.

01:23.834 --> 01:24.869
And then I blink...

01:25.043 --> 01:28.786
...all of a sudden, I'm this under-qualiﬁed
shrink for meteor-infected kids...

01:28.964 --> 01:31.330
...who will probably wake up
to be psycho killers...

01:31.508 --> 01:36.343
...while Lois and Clark are walking the beat
with matching press passes together.

01:36.513 --> 01:40.301
Oh, and did I mention that l was actually
able to hold on to happily ever after...

01:40.476 --> 01:44.344
...for about 2.3 seconds
before my marriage imploded?

01:45.397 --> 01:48.639
Is this the part where you belt out the aria
and drive a dagger into your corset?

01:48.817 --> 01:50.023
[CHLOE SIGHS]

01:51.195 --> 01:53.937
All right, sorry for the operetta.

01:54.114 --> 01:57.277
It's just-- I would love to know
how she does it.

01:58.702 --> 02:02.786
Chloe, if I didn't know you better,
I'd say there was a hint of jealousy in there.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.571
No.

02:04.875 --> 02:06.160
It's just--

02:06.335 --> 02:09.327
With all these Debbie ups and downers
lately...

02:09.505 --> 02:13.589
...I guess it would be really nice to leave
it all behind and be back in the bullpen.

02:14.551 --> 02:16.052
Ex; 2:1:

02:17.888 --> 02:20.630
One year closer
to the sweet release of death.

02:21.350 --> 02:22.760
How wonderfully morbid.

02:22.935 --> 02:24.300
LOIS:
Chloe, I am so sorry.

02:24.478 --> 02:27.015
There's been a factory workers revolt
in Mexico City...

02:27.189 --> 02:30.272
...and the Planet is ﬂying me down,
el primero class-o.

02:30.442 --> 02:31.557
Wheels up in 30.

02:33.821 --> 02:35.937
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

02:36.114 --> 02:37.570
Love you.

02:37.741 --> 02:39.072
[SCOFFS]

02:50.546 --> 02:53.583
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

02:54.216 --> 02:55.251
Oh, Chloe, I got to—

02:55.425 --> 02:56.551
Duty calls.

02:56.718 --> 02:57.753
It's ﬁne.

02:58.595 --> 03:00.460
I'm
sorry

03:00.806 --> 03:02.421
Happy birthday.

03:04.560 --> 03:08.098
There's a man who looks like he needs
a little magic in his button-up life.

03:08.480 --> 03:12.644
Uh, you know what? I wouldn't wanna steal
the hocus-pocus from the birthday girl.

03:12.818 --> 03:16.356
How about a little something special for
the someone who truly deserves it, okay?

03:16.530 --> 03:17.940
CHLOE:
Mm—hm.

03:24.621 --> 03:25.906
Rough birthday, huh?

03:26.415 --> 03:29.452
You ever seen the napalm scene
in Apocalypse Now?

03:29.626 --> 03:32.038
More ﬁre. Less cake.

03:32.212 --> 03:34.294
Let's make sure tomorrow's a better day,
hmm?

03:38.260 --> 03:39.295
Make a wish.

03:47.477 --> 03:50.059
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

04:04.286 --> 04:06.322
[SIGHS]

04:31.438 --> 04:33.679
Oh, my God, I'm Lois.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.078
[SIGHS]

05:36.253 --> 05:38.790
So everything's okay with you in Mexico,
Lois?

05:38.964 --> 05:42.832
Everything is great, except for government
oppression and slave labor. Why?

05:43.510 --> 05:45.421
Uh....

05:45.595 --> 05:47.586
It's just, uh--

05:47.764 --> 05:49.265
You sure?

05:49.433 --> 05:51.344
-Nothing weird?
-No. Chlo...

05:52.185 --> 05:54.676
...what is going on?
You don't sound like yourself.

05:56.398 --> 05:58.730
No. Uh, me?

05:59.317 --> 06:01.603
Just got a frog in my throat.

06:02.612 --> 06:03.863
Okay.

06:04.031 --> 06:05.362
Well, you take care.

06:06.616 --> 06:08.402
You too.

06:08.785 --> 06:10.070
[PHONE BEEPS]

06:16.501 --> 06:19.959
MAN: Hey, Lois.
-Nice job on that city hall piece, Lane.

06:20.839 --> 06:23.751
Dry cleaning and your morning coffee,
Miss Lane.

06:25.969 --> 06:27.800
Thanks. Um....

06:27.971 --> 06:30.758
Don't worry, Miss Lane. You'll remember
my name one of these days.

06:31.266 --> 06:32.676
[SIGHS]

06:34.936 --> 06:36.392
[SIGHS]

06:38.148 --> 06:39.888
Right.

06:48.617 --> 06:49.982
[SIGHS]

07:08.053 --> 07:09.589
[SIGHS]

07:18.605 --> 07:19.845
Lois?

07:21.191 --> 07:22.522
Thank God, Clark.

07:22.692 --> 07:26.025
You couldn't have been deported
that quickly. Why aren't you in Mexico?

07:27.072 --> 07:30.860
Isn't there a limit to how tight a shirt
can be and meet dress code?

07:31.201 --> 07:32.862
Really?

07:33.036 --> 07:34.196
Even you?

07:34.371 --> 07:35.486
Well—

07:35.664 --> 07:36.870
Here's the thing.

07:37.207 --> 07:38.993
I never made it to Mexico.

07:39.167 --> 07:42.876
Can this wait until after your post-lunch,
pre-dinner, after-coffee snack break?

07:44.381 --> 07:47.293
Can't imagine you'd have anything
more to say after last night.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.298
Last night?

07:49.469 --> 07:51.676
Yeah, you called me ﬁve times
from the airport.

07:51.847 --> 07:52.962
One from the airplane.

07:53.140 --> 07:57.804
You had time to answer six phone calls
and you couldn't call Chloe on her birthday?

07:57.978 --> 08:01.391
Chloe knows sometimes I get hung up
with the farm.

08:01.565 --> 08:05.899
If this attitude is because you think
I'm taking Jimmy's side on the breakup...

08:06.069 --> 08:09.186
...it's because I believe there are two sides
to every story.

08:11.324 --> 08:13.906
Really? Exactly what two sides?

08:14.744 --> 08:17.531
Look, he may have gone overboard
on the whole...

08:17.831 --> 08:20.743
...Davis Bloome-serial-killer thing.

08:20.917 --> 08:25.581
It's tough when the person you're trying to
build your life with doesn't believe in you.

08:28.508 --> 08:29.918
Lois, are you all right?

08:31.761 --> 08:34.924
No, I am deﬁnitely not all right.

08:35.098 --> 08:36.554
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

08:36.725 --> 08:41.094
Well, this should help. Police standoff.
Main and Fifth. Grab yourjacket.

08:43.523 --> 08:46.265
Isn't this the part
where you tell me to saddle up?

08:49.404 --> 08:52.020
Start your engines, Smallville.

09:22.729 --> 09:26.893
Now, why do I get the feeling
you're not my 10:00 from the steel union?

09:27.651 --> 09:29.312
Zatanna.

09:29.986 --> 09:31.647
We weren't properly introduced.

09:31.821 --> 09:32.901
Zatanna.

09:33.073 --> 09:35.280
-You lose a bet with that name?
-Ha, ha.

09:35.450 --> 09:37.782
-lt's a family thing.
-Okay.

09:37.953 --> 09:41.116
So, uh, Zatanna— Is it? Right.

09:41.289 --> 09:43.575
You mind telling me what drives
a lovely woman...

09:43.750 --> 09:48.289
...to track down an unsuspecting CEO
at a night club and then again at his ofﬁce?

09:48.838 --> 09:49.998
I need your help.

09:50.382 --> 09:52.088
You don't scream charity case.

09:52.259 --> 09:53.294
[CH UCKLES]

09:53.468 --> 09:57.837
My father left me an estate in Shadowcrest
so money isn't an object.

10:00.809 --> 10:03.141
Shadowcrest?

10:06.940 --> 10:08.646
John Zatara...

10:08.817 --> 10:10.808
...the Maestro of Magic,
he was your father?

10:14.197 --> 10:16.779
Well, I'm sorry.
I know what it's like to lose family.

10:17.325 --> 10:18.610
Yeah.

10:18.785 --> 10:21.151
I lost more than my father.

10:21.329 --> 10:22.739
I lost his entire legacy...

10:22.914 --> 10:26.532
...recorded in a book that's been passed
down through generations.

10:26.710 --> 10:30.623
There's a bible's worth of my heritage
in those pages.

10:30.964 --> 10:34.127
When my father died,
Mr. Luthor acquired that book at auction.

10:37.762 --> 10:39.718
Well, no offense, Zatanna...

10:39.889 --> 10:42.505
...but, uh, you're the
daughter of the world's greatest magician...

10:42.684 --> 10:45.050
...can't you just, I don't know,
wiggle your nose...

10:45.228 --> 10:47.765
...and pull it out of a hat or something?

10:48.398 --> 10:49.888
You're cute.

10:50.066 --> 10:51.181
And, no.

10:51.359 --> 10:56.149
My father refused to teach me
much beyond practical parlor tricks.

10:56.448 --> 10:58.905
Oh. Uh....

10:59.242 --> 11:01.403
Well, I'm sorry, I really wish I could help.

11:01.578 --> 11:04.741
Queen Industries may have absorbed
all of LuthorCorp's holdings...

11:04.914 --> 11:09.078
...but I'm afraid Lex's lawyers won't let me
anywhere near his private collection.

11:10.253 --> 11:13.370
I thought I was gonna have
to use a little incentive.

11:14.758 --> 11:17.249
See, I have the ability to grant one wish.

11:17.427 --> 11:21.170
Big or small, whatever you wish for
in that moment, it can be yours.

11:26.561 --> 11:28.802
Well, that's very tempting...

11:28.980 --> 11:31.767
...but as you can see,
I'm pretty comfortable with my life.

11:31.941 --> 11:34.432
Well, there has to be somebody
you've lost...

11:34.611 --> 11:37.944
...something that you've done
that you wish you could take back.

11:39.574 --> 11:42.532
Get me my book and I'll make it happen.

11:44.579 --> 11:45.785
Offer expires at midnight.

12:01.971 --> 12:04.383
CLARK: You haven't insulted me today.
LOIS: Aah!

12:04.557 --> 12:06.889
And you actually crossed
at the cross walk.

12:07.060 --> 12:09.767
-Did Jeff not bring you your coffee today?
-Uh....

12:09.938 --> 12:13.146
Let's just say I rolled out of bed
on the right side.

12:13.316 --> 12:17.480
It's amazing how much more you can see
with fresh eyes.

12:17.654 --> 12:19.770
So anything else you aren't telling Chloe?

12:19.948 --> 12:21.279
Whoa!

12:24.911 --> 12:26.822
What's the look for?

12:27.580 --> 12:29.081
Uh....

12:29.332 --> 12:33.041
You've just never looked at me
that way before.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.500
[CHLOE GASPS]

12:38.675 --> 12:40.006
[MAN SPEAKS IN LATIN
OVER MEGAPHONE]

12:40.176 --> 12:42.132
Oh, there's our story calling.

12:42.303 --> 12:45.170
[MAN SPEAKING IN LATIN
ON MEGAPHONE]

12:45.348 --> 12:47.805
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

12:55.191 --> 12:58.183
Technically, it still is a standoff.

12:58.611 --> 13:00.021
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

13:01.531 --> 13:04.819
All right, Lane, this squares us up
before Friday night's poker game...

13:04.993 --> 13:07.985
...and by the way,
I've been working on my bluff, okay?

13:09.080 --> 13:12.197
Right.
Keep up the good work there, tough guy.

13:14.043 --> 13:17.535
Ha, ha. So, what's the deal
with our Sophoclean town crier up there?

13:19.340 --> 13:21.467
Yeah, well, here's the situation.

13:21.634 --> 13:26.253
The nut-job up there on the ﬁre escape, he
owns Yuri's Antiques over on Main Street.

13:26.431 --> 13:29.218
He's been babbling in Latin all day.

13:31.102 --> 13:33.058
I'll see you on Friday.

13:33.229 --> 13:36.062
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

13:38.193 --> 13:41.401
Woman, magic, cursed tongue...

13:41.571 --> 13:42.606
...book brings death.

13:42.780 --> 13:44.987
Since when did you speak Latin?

13:45.158 --> 13:46.568
Zatanna!

13:46.743 --> 13:48.074
Zatanna!

13:49.120 --> 13:50.951
Zatanna.

13:51.122 --> 13:52.623
Clark.

13:53.333 --> 13:56.166
I bet it is that same witchy-woman
who did this to me.

13:56.336 --> 13:57.746
I know where she's performing.

13:57.921 --> 14:02.290
Maybe you can super-speed over to this
antique shop and dust off any leads.

14:02.509 --> 14:05.091
Super-speed? We didn't even bring a car.

14:05.637 --> 14:07.047
What?

14:07.514 --> 14:10.051
It's okay. I'm Chloe.

14:13.144 --> 14:15.385
Stood-her-up-at-formal Chloe.

14:15.563 --> 14:19.055
Planted-one-on-you-because-Zod
was-ending-the-world Chloe.

14:19.234 --> 14:22.317
Krypton, Jor-El, fortress, brainiac Chloe.

14:22.487 --> 14:23.727
-Chloe.
-Bingo.

14:24.572 --> 14:26.949
Just like that raving wardrobe
malfunction over there...

14:27.116 --> 14:30.449
...some magician showed up at my birthday
party in ﬁshnets and hexed me.

14:30.620 --> 14:34.112
But you'd know that if you hadn't skipped it
to answer voicemails from Lois.

14:34.290 --> 14:35.450
[CHLOE SIGHS]

14:35.625 --> 14:37.536
Not that I'm dwelling.

14:44.300 --> 14:45.915
Not exactly hiding out, is she?

14:46.094 --> 14:47.379
You just woke up like this?

14:47.554 --> 14:49.294
How did I not pick up on it sooner?

14:49.472 --> 14:52.305
Forget about it,
this is my Shakespearean nightmare...

14:52.475 --> 14:54.431
...not yours.

14:54.769 --> 14:57.636
Although it has been awfully illuminating.

14:57.814 --> 14:59.896
Listen, what I said about Jimmy....

15:00.066 --> 15:02.307
You're an equal-opportunity good guy,
I get it.

15:02.485 --> 15:05.602
I guess I'm just not used to seeing you
from this perspective.

15:05.780 --> 15:09.489
By the way,
Tales of the Weird & Unexplained?

15:10.451 --> 15:11.907
Nice callback.

15:12.078 --> 15:14.740
It might bring you back to a time
when things were—

15:14.914 --> 15:16.324
Weird and unexplained?

15:17.917 --> 15:19.782
You sound like you miss it.

15:20.295 --> 15:22.160
I don't know.

15:22.964 --> 15:26.502
It's just there's a whole half of my life
where this happens.

15:26.676 --> 15:28.507
Every day.

15:29.679 --> 15:32.421
Weird has become so normal,
it's not even weird anymore.

15:33.433 --> 15:35.674
Honestly, I like what I'm doing
at the Planet now.

15:36.102 --> 15:38.184
But I'd be lying if I said
there weren't days...

15:38.354 --> 15:41.721
...when I wish I'd forget about saving
the world and just be a normal reporter.

15:41.899 --> 15:43.605
[CHLOE SIGHS]

15:43.860 --> 15:47.102
Well, for now,
how about you not stick to your day job?

15:51.868 --> 15:53.028
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:56.873 --> 15:58.613
It won't be much longer, Father.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.827
CLARK:
Much longer for what?

16:03.963 --> 16:05.624
I'm
sorry

16:06.382 --> 16:07.371
Have we met?

16:07.967 --> 16:11.050
Ha, ha, does an enchanted cupcake
ring any bells?

16:11.888 --> 16:13.879
You were the birthday girl.

16:14.390 --> 16:17.382
You need to reverse the curse
that you put on Chloe.

16:17.977 --> 16:19.558
Curse?

16:19.729 --> 16:21.811
Is that what you think happened?

16:22.565 --> 16:24.226
Kind of got things backwards.

16:24.400 --> 16:25.810
l granted you a wish.

16:26.486 --> 16:27.521
[CH UCKLES]

16:27.695 --> 16:30.732
Why on Earth would I wish myself
into this?

16:30.907 --> 16:32.192
Beats me.

16:32.367 --> 16:34.608
I don't write the magics, honey,
I just use them.

16:34.786 --> 16:38.370
Now, I'm not saying
this is your heart's deepest desire...

16:38.915 --> 16:40.906
...but in that moment...

16:41.250 --> 16:42.706
...this is what you wanted.

16:45.171 --> 16:47.002
Okay, just for a second...

16:47.173 --> 16:51.963
...maybe I was a little jealous of Lois living
my dream life with Clark at the Planet...

16:52.136 --> 16:55.094
...but I didn't literally want her life.

16:55.264 --> 16:56.674
Not like this.

16:57.016 --> 17:00.258
Well, don't worry, it'll wear off
as soon as you don't want it anymore.

17:00.978 --> 17:02.639
[SIGHS]

17:07.443 --> 17:09.274
Fine.

17:09.946 --> 17:11.686
I don't want it.

17:13.616 --> 17:14.947
[CH UCKLES]

17:15.118 --> 17:17.109
You keep telling yourself that.

17:19.747 --> 17:22.124
You really think that man
from the antique shop...

17:22.291 --> 17:25.203
...wanted to end up rambling on
like a crazy person?

17:28.798 --> 17:31.790
Maybe he wanted a better understanding
of dead languages.

17:31.968 --> 17:33.799
I wanted an heirloom of my father's.

17:33.970 --> 17:35.676
We helped each other out.

17:35.847 --> 17:36.882
Fair trade.

17:37.265 --> 17:38.425
About that heirloom...

17:39.642 --> 17:44.056
...what did Yuri mean when he said
that book you were after would bring death?

17:45.314 --> 17:47.896
Some people can be a little superstitious.

17:48.860 --> 17:50.566
And that makes it okay to use them?

17:53.740 --> 17:54.820
Use them?

17:54.991 --> 17:57.152
I give people what they want.

17:58.995 --> 18:02.829
Look, everybody has something
they're hoping for.

18:02.999 --> 18:04.330
Something--

18:04.500 --> 18:06.912
Something they wish they could change.

18:09.046 --> 18:10.707
Even you.

18:13.593 --> 18:15.959
I wonder what your little wish would be.

18:16.137 --> 18:17.502
[MAGIC CHIMES]

18:19.682 --> 18:21.297
CHLOE:
Clark.

18:21.851 --> 18:23.842
Oh, no. Clark.

18:28.191 --> 18:29.681
Are you okay?

18:30.735 --> 18:32.521
I'm ﬁne.

18:33.863 --> 18:35.023
Really?

18:37.700 --> 18:40.066
Something has to be different.

18:47.043 --> 18:50.376
I never should have brought you along.
Magic affects you just like us.

18:50.546 --> 18:52.832
-Are you sure you're all right?
-Yes, Lois, stop asking.

18:53.007 --> 18:55.714
-What do you mean by the rest of us?
-lt's just that--

18:56.219 --> 18:57.880
Wait.

18:59.931 --> 19:01.046
What did you just call me?

19:01.224 --> 19:02.885
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

19:03.810 --> 19:05.095
WOMAN:
Let me go!

19:05.269 --> 19:06.884
lib}

19:08.147 --> 19:10.308
Aren't you gonna do anything?

19:13.861 --> 19:16.102
You're absolutely right, Lois.

19:17.740 --> 19:19.480
911?

19:22.995 --> 19:25.577
How gullible do you think I am, Lois?

19:25.748 --> 19:26.737
I'm Chloe.

19:26.916 --> 19:30.784
Right. At ﬁrst, I had trouble telling
you two apart as well. Lois is the tall one.

19:30.962 --> 19:33.749
You acknowledged I was Chloe
before our run-in with Zatanna.

19:33.923 --> 19:37.336
-She bibbidi-bobbidi-boo'd you too.
-Lois, there's no such thing as magic.

19:37.510 --> 19:39.341
It's all trap doors and wires.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.252
Okay, Clark, think about it.

19:41.430 --> 19:44.342
You were just complaining
about how easy it would be...

19:44.517 --> 19:48.135
...if you could just forget the whole hero,
alien, everything weird side...

19:48.312 --> 19:51.224
...were just a regular,
mundane reporter living a normal life.

19:51.399 --> 19:54.391
Something seems too weird to be true,
it usually is.

19:56.904 --> 19:58.235
It's rule number four.

19:59.699 --> 20:00.779
What?

20:03.536 --> 20:04.571
[CLARK SIGHS]

20:04.745 --> 20:07.077
CLARK:
Lois Lane Rules of Reporting.

20:07.248 --> 20:09.079
Come on, like you'd ever let me forget.

20:12.753 --> 20:13.959
And you framed this?

20:15.965 --> 20:19.002
Look, you said you wanted only one
of your double lives...

20:19.176 --> 20:23.089
...and whether you meant it or not,
the spell thought you did.

20:23.764 --> 20:26.597
Exactly what other life is it
I'm supposed to have, Lois?

20:35.067 --> 20:38.230
Lois, what has gotten into you?

20:39.322 --> 20:42.314
Now wait a second,
we're not allowed to be up here, Lois.

20:43.200 --> 20:44.940
Clark...

20:45.244 --> 20:46.484
...snap out of it.

20:49.373 --> 20:50.988
You're a hero.

20:51.167 --> 20:53.658
Ha, ha. I'm a regular Green Arrow.

20:53.836 --> 20:55.701
Lois, I don't make the news.

20:55.880 --> 20:57.245
| just report it.

20:58.466 --> 21:01.549
You are the biggest news there is.

21:01.719 --> 21:04.176
You're a superhuman being
from another planet.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.092
Okay, just don't tell Human Resources,
all right?

21:07.266 --> 21:10.178
-Now, I have a deadline to meet.
-Uh....

21:11.687 --> 21:13.097
[DOOR LOCK CLICKS]

21:16.692 --> 21:18.353
Did you just lock us up here?

21:18.736 --> 21:20.272
Open the door, Clark.

21:20.446 --> 21:21.606
[SIGHS]

21:21.822 --> 21:23.858
Lois, it's locked. We need a key.

21:24.033 --> 21:27.025
-Open the damned door, Clark.
-Lois--

21:31.916 --> 21:34.032
Now, do you believe me?

21:34.210 --> 21:37.452
What I believe is that this door
needs better maintenance.

21:37.630 --> 21:41.043
Look at the rust in here,
no wonder it just pulled off like that.

21:41.217 --> 21:42.377
Okay.

21:42.551 --> 21:45.008
-Now we're gonna be stuck up here.
-How about this?

21:47.390 --> 21:50.302
Listen, really listen.

21:51.268 --> 21:52.553
What do you hear?

21:52.728 --> 21:55.640
[JACK HAMMER DRILLING]

21:57.316 --> 22:00.183
[CAR HONKING]

22:01.404 --> 22:03.861
[SIREN WAILING]

22:04.031 --> 22:07.740
[CROWD CHATTERING]

22:14.041 --> 22:18.159
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

22:21.966 --> 22:23.081
That's amazing.

22:25.219 --> 22:27.380
The acoustics up here are incredible.

22:27.555 --> 22:31.343
It's like there's some perfect echo point,
right here.

22:31.517 --> 22:32.848
-And--
-Unh!

22:33.019 --> 22:35.260
Lois, have you completely
lost your mind?

22:35.438 --> 22:37.429
-That could have really hurt.
-No, it—

22:39.734 --> 22:41.099
[PIPE CLANGS]

22:43.362 --> 22:45.023
No, it wouldn't, Clark.

22:45.531 --> 22:49.945
You've got super-speed and super-strength
and super-hearing and x-ray vision.

22:50.119 --> 22:53.202
And l have a deadline, Lois.
Now, please, if you would excuse me...

22:53.372 --> 22:56.034
...I need to ﬁnd a way
to get off this roof.

22:56.208 --> 23:01.453
Unless my super-powers
include an ability to ﬂy.

23:02.757 --> 23:04.122
[SIGHS]

23:05.926 --> 23:07.632
I didn't think so.

23:12.141 --> 23:14.132
[SIGHS]

23:21.609 --> 23:22.689
[ARROW THUDS]

23:22.860 --> 23:25.317
[ALARM BEEPING]

23:29.950 --> 23:31.326
[BEEPING INTENSIFIES]

23:32.244 --> 23:33.745
[GUARDS GRUNT]

23:40.294 --> 23:41.830
Sorry, guys.

23:42.004 --> 23:44.666
I'll make sure
you get a nice Christmas bonus.

24:20.376 --> 24:22.037
Thanks, Lex.

24:28.175 --> 24:29.711
[MAGIC CHIMES]

24:33.097 --> 24:37.181
Bravo, you found my book
and pulled it off in style.

24:39.186 --> 24:42.223
-I wish I could say I've had the pleasure.
-Ha, ha.

24:42.398 --> 24:44.605
Oh, please, Oliver.

24:44.775 --> 24:49.860
Ask a billionaire for help and then
a vigilante steals exactly what I ask for?

24:50.030 --> 24:52.066
You need to work
on your sleight of hand.

24:59.165 --> 25:00.530
Yeah.

25:03.794 --> 25:08.538
Now, give me my book
and I'll give you your wish.

25:08.716 --> 25:10.252
A deal's a deal.

25:11.260 --> 25:15.253
You know, this isn'tjust a how-to guide
on upping your stage presence.

25:15.431 --> 25:17.888
There's some really dark stuff in here,
Zatanna.

25:18.475 --> 25:19.931
You don't get it.

25:20.102 --> 25:24.186
The sick irony of my ability
is that I can grant so many wishes.

25:24.356 --> 25:26.768
Everyone's but mine.

25:32.031 --> 25:33.441
No.

25:33.616 --> 25:36.449
Please don't.

25:37.745 --> 25:40.282
It's the only way
I can bring my father back.

25:46.545 --> 25:48.285
I'm
sorry

25:53.594 --> 25:54.629
Not good.

25:54.803 --> 25:56.134
[ZATANNA CHANTS
IN MAGICAL LANGUAGE]

25:58.349 --> 26:00.761
[CHAINS CLANG]

26:00.935 --> 26:03.051
[GREEN ARROW GRUNTING]

26:05.814 --> 26:07.145
You don't wanna do this.

26:08.484 --> 26:11.191
You can't just bring someone back
and change fate.

26:11.362 --> 26:12.818
I'm
sorry

26:12.988 --> 26:15.479
I've waited too long for this.

26:18.494 --> 26:20.826
-l'm coming, Father.
-Unh!

26:21.372 --> 26:22.407
[GRUNTS]

26:35.761 --> 26:37.843
l'll handle this, Lois.

26:42.685 --> 26:44.175
[CLARK CLEARS THROAT]

26:44.895 --> 26:46.351
Do you speak English?

26:46.855 --> 26:49.767
Yes. You mind telling me who you are?

26:50.609 --> 26:53.316
Lois Lane, Daily Planet.

26:54.029 --> 26:57.863
I'm sorry, we thought you were under
some kind of spell.

26:58.325 --> 26:59.531
Well, she did.

27:01.662 --> 27:02.868
You know?

27:03.038 --> 27:04.653
We know Zatanna gave you a wish...

27:04.832 --> 27:07.198
...in exchange for some information
on a book.

27:07.376 --> 27:10.288
I never should have told her
how to ﬁnd that book.

27:10.462 --> 27:14.205
I'm afraid she's too blinded by her grief
to see the danger that she's in.

27:15.926 --> 27:19.384
Say this woman does know magic,
what sort of danger are you talking about?

27:19.555 --> 27:23.548
She must to be stopped from using
that book to resurrect her father.

27:23.726 --> 27:25.637
She isn't prepared to make the sacriﬁce.

27:25.811 --> 27:27.142
What kind of sacriﬁce?

27:28.439 --> 27:31.522
From what I could decipher,
the incantation to bring a life back...

27:31.692 --> 27:33.978
...required the taking of a life in return.

27:34.153 --> 27:37.816
So in order to bring her father back,
someone else must die?

27:39.158 --> 27:40.398
A life for a life.

27:44.079 --> 27:45.740
A soul for a soul.

28:03.724 --> 28:10.687
"As life is lived from front to back,
let death be turned back to front."

28:11.565 --> 28:13.351
Grant me my wish.

28:13.525 --> 28:16.983
Resurrect John Zatara.

28:17.279 --> 28:20.817
[CHANTS IN MAGICAL LANGUAGE]

28:26.997 --> 28:29.613
That guy really sounded like he believed
in what he was saying.

28:29.792 --> 28:31.123
That's because it was true.

28:31.293 --> 28:34.535
We need to ﬁnd Zatanna before she tries
to give dear old dad one ﬁnal encore.

28:34.713 --> 28:36.044
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

28:36.215 --> 28:37.625
Looks like we may be too late.

28:42.429 --> 28:46.297
Clark, you're the only person who can get
up there and put an end to this right now.

28:46.475 --> 28:50.809
-I know what you're gonna say, but--
-No, Clark, there are no buts with you.

28:50.979 --> 28:52.560
No exception to the rule.

28:53.440 --> 28:55.977
Now, super-leap up there and stop her.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.237
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

28:59.738 --> 29:00.853
Look, I don't know, it--

29:01.031 --> 29:03.898
Yeah, okay.
Okay, Clark, you don't have to know.

29:04.076 --> 29:06.943
If you won't believe in yourself,
then let me believe in you.

29:07.788 --> 29:14.000
Okay? I know that deep inside,
you don't wanna just be a normal guy...

29:14.169 --> 29:17.002
...sitting behind a desk,
reporting on disasters...

29:17.339 --> 29:19.500
...while you could be out there
stopping them.

29:21.218 --> 29:23.880
Now use the power you feel.

29:27.349 --> 29:30.512
The world needs you.

29:36.525 --> 29:38.436
[MAGIC CHIMES]

29:41.530 --> 29:42.690
Chloe?

29:42.865 --> 29:44.776
-Wait, that's--
-lmpossible?

29:44.950 --> 29:46.315
Only in your mind.

29:46.493 --> 29:48.609
Sometimes you just need
a little leap of faith.

29:49.705 --> 29:51.241
Come on, Clark.

29:51.415 --> 29:53.371
You can do this.

29:54.835 --> 29:56.996
Up, up and away.

30:12.144 --> 30:13.350
Daddy?

30:13.520 --> 30:16.557
Zatanna, you need to stop this spell.

30:16.732 --> 30:18.142
Don't move.

30:18.317 --> 30:19.853
I need to bring my father back.

30:20.027 --> 30:21.858
At what cost?

30:23.447 --> 30:26.029
Are you willing to sacriﬁce your life
for him?

30:26.200 --> 30:28.031
It's what he did for me.

30:29.077 --> 30:31.568
He wasn't meant to die.

30:32.080 --> 30:34.162
I owe him this.

30:34.583 --> 30:36.414
I know the rules.

30:36.960 --> 30:38.496
A life for a life.

30:40.255 --> 30:41.756
l have to make it right.

30:44.718 --> 30:45.833
I'm not afraid.

30:46.011 --> 30:49.595
Your father would want you to give up
the life he gave you to bring him back?

30:49.765 --> 30:53.678
What would you know about losing
the one man who made you who you are?

30:55.270 --> 30:57.886
The day that I lost my father...

30:58.065 --> 31:00.852
...I thought my world
would never be the same.

31:02.110 --> 31:05.602
It felt like something had been ripped away
from me forever.

31:06.490 --> 31:08.071
But I had to let him go.

31:16.792 --> 31:18.248
Chloe!

31:18.418 --> 31:21.205
No. No, it was supposed to be me.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.745
We don't get to choose.

31:23.924 --> 31:27.291
But we do get to choose
how we live the life that we've been given.

31:29.179 --> 31:32.387
I'm ﬁnally the man
that my father wanted me to be.

31:33.934 --> 31:36.300
Who does your father want you to be?

31:45.654 --> 31:47.610
I'm
sorry

31:58.292 --> 32:00.123
Close the door.

32:01.128 --> 32:04.245
[CHANTS IN MAGICAL LANGUAGE]

32:09.761 --> 32:11.342
Chloe?

32:35.871 --> 32:37.702
[CH UCKLES]

32:39.166 --> 32:40.201
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

32:41.710 --> 32:44.497
Peace offering for missing your party.

32:45.339 --> 32:47.455
Casualties of being a hero.

32:47.633 --> 32:51.546
Not everyone could have punched through
Zatanna's whammy and saved the day.

32:52.763 --> 32:54.754
I couldn't have done it without you.

32:54.931 --> 32:57.138
Thank you for reminding me
who I really am.

32:57.309 --> 33:01.473
Yeah, I guess rebooting your superhero OS
rekindled the Chloe-ﬁre.

33:03.190 --> 33:06.682
Looks like, uh, hero-support
isn't just a day job anymore.

33:07.444 --> 33:08.524
And for that...

33:09.404 --> 33:10.905
...we eat bagels.

33:11.406 --> 33:13.397
Do you remember everything?

33:13.575 --> 33:16.066
If you're referring
to the just-the-facts-ma'am routine...

33:16.703 --> 33:18.159
[CH UCKLES]

33:19.414 --> 33:21.496
...it did feel as though a weight
had been lifted.

33:22.042 --> 33:23.077
Hmm.

33:23.251 --> 33:25.162
It must have been hard
to harness up again.

33:25.754 --> 33:29.246
To be honest, a life without responsibility
kind of felt empty.

33:29.424 --> 33:31.540
I mean, this is who I am, Chloe.

33:31.718 --> 33:34.255
Every morning, I wake up with a purpose.

33:34.930 --> 33:38.548
Yeah, you're not the only one who saw
the world through irony-colored glasses.

33:42.062 --> 33:44.769
Why'd you wait so long
to tell me what was going on?

33:48.360 --> 33:52.603
Let's face it, Clark, my life has been
a little less than desirable lately.

33:53.115 --> 33:55.948
-I mean, with Jimmy and everything.
-Chloe--

33:56.118 --> 34:01.909
And I can't deny there's an appeal
to the dynamic duo's weekly adventures.

34:02.082 --> 34:03.447
Well, you haven't missed much.

34:03.625 --> 34:06.617
Things haven't exactly been smooth
between us lately.

34:06.795 --> 34:11.710
I know you don't wanna open a can of
Kryptonian worms by telling her your secret.

34:11.883 --> 34:16.422
But whether you like it or not,
Lois Lane is a part of your life now.

34:17.848 --> 34:21.511
And considering
the nonstop puppy dog eyes you give her...

34:21.685 --> 34:24.973
...l'm guessing you don't mind much
at all.

34:27.399 --> 34:30.232
Clark,
just because you were burned once...

34:30.402 --> 34:33.144
...doesn't mean that you can't give it
a second chance.

34:35.073 --> 34:37.485
Are we still talking about me...

34:38.493 --> 34:40.324
...or are we talking about you
and Jimmy?

34:44.332 --> 34:46.072
Touché.

34:47.085 --> 34:50.998
Okay, I'm talking about neither of us
living in the past.

34:52.340 --> 34:54.331
You can never be who you wanna be...

34:54.509 --> 34:57.797
...if you're always looking
over your shoulder at what could have been.

35:02.976 --> 35:04.841
Cheers to that.

35:16.573 --> 35:18.734
What is this,
you drop by to kick my ass again?

35:18.909 --> 35:21.025
It was so much fun for me the ﬁrst time.

35:21.203 --> 35:22.909
I came to apologize.

35:23.079 --> 35:25.331
-I just—
-Bound by steel.

35:25.499 --> 35:27.956
That's what you said to me, backwards.
Bound by steel.

35:28.126 --> 35:31.038
I had plenty of time to mull that over
when you, uh, left me there...

35:31.213 --> 35:34.205
...strung up to either die
or have my identity revealed.

35:35.091 --> 35:38.174
I can't ever totally make it up to you
or your friends...

35:38.345 --> 35:42.054
...but I'd like to try to make sure
something like this doesn't happen again.

35:42.224 --> 35:43.430
Here's a thought:

35:43.600 --> 35:45.465
Don't do it again.

35:46.895 --> 35:49.352
Hold on a second.

35:56.321 --> 36:00.234
I know how difﬁcult the sacriﬁces you made
must have been.

36:01.576 --> 36:05.034
Especially considering how hell-bent
you were on getting what you wanted.

36:05.747 --> 36:08.784
Well, anyway, in the end,
you made the tough choice...

36:10.252 --> 36:12.243
...and, um, I can respect that.

36:15.590 --> 36:20.254
Just know that there are far more dangerous
people out there in the world than me...

36:20.428 --> 36:24.216
...people with much greater control
of the genuinely nasty magics than I do.

36:26.101 --> 36:27.511
So...

36:27.936 --> 36:31.679
...if you ever run
into my kind of mischief again...

36:32.023 --> 36:33.559
...call me...

36:33.900 --> 36:38.109
...and wherever I am,
this time I'm on your side.

36:38.280 --> 36:41.238
So I guess this means
you're taking your show on the road.

36:41.783 --> 36:46.402
Thinking about taking a little bit of time off
to do some light reading.

36:46.997 --> 36:49.613
If I'm ever gonna do my father proud...

36:49.791 --> 36:52.373
...l've got a lot of catching up to do.

36:58.008 --> 36:59.123
Uh....

36:59.301 --> 37:00.791
So...

37:00.969 --> 37:04.461
...what is this, exactly?
Some kind of magic spell to summon you?

37:04.639 --> 37:09.099
| just hold it up, say your name
a couple times and, uh, poof, you appear?

37:09.644 --> 37:11.851
It's my phone number.

37:14.524 --> 37:15.855
Oh.

37:16.443 --> 37:17.979
[WHISPERS]
Of course it is.

37:20.071 --> 37:22.483
[MAGIC CHIMES]

37:35.462 --> 37:37.953
[CHAIR CREAKING]

37:40.800 --> 37:43.382
[CHAIR CREAKING]

37:46.973 --> 37:49.259
Is there something on your mind, Lois?

37:50.810 --> 37:54.974
So how long did it take for you to realize
that I wasn't my usual, charming self?

37:56.358 --> 37:59.145
Well, I have to admit,
I should have picked up on it sooner.

37:59.319 --> 38:00.855
You weren't as bossy as usual...

38:02.656 --> 38:05.022
...and Chloe let me drive.

38:05.700 --> 38:07.315
Well...

38:07.619 --> 38:11.703
...little blond sources tell me
that you don't mind my assertive ﬂair.

38:15.251 --> 38:17.207
[SIGHS]

38:17.379 --> 38:18.664
Let me see it.

38:20.298 --> 38:22.835
Lois, I don't know
what you're talking about.

38:24.970 --> 38:27.882
You have a terrible poker face, Smallville.

38:31.184 --> 38:32.424
[SIGHS]

38:32.602 --> 38:34.263
Give me. Give me.

38:34.646 --> 38:36.477
[CLARK SIGHS]

38:46.866 --> 38:48.367
Wow.

38:48.576 --> 38:50.828
Who would have known
you were this sentimental?

38:53.164 --> 38:57.874
I think we should hang it up
so that everyone can see it.

38:58.211 --> 39:01.669
This is a memento
from my ﬁrst day on the job.

39:04.050 --> 39:06.883
And a constant reminder
there's only one Lois Lane.

39:09.723 --> 39:11.259
You better believe it.

39:16.229 --> 39:17.514
Big night?

39:17.689 --> 39:22.433
Hmm, yeah, this guy in ﬁrst class asked me
out and I ﬁgured, why the hell not, right?

39:23.862 --> 39:25.272
Right.

39:26.656 --> 39:29.068
What about you? Big plans?

39:29.576 --> 39:32.784
Uh, I'm just gonna hang around here,
you know, follow up on a few things.

39:32.954 --> 39:35.411
Want me to call
if anything comes through the wire?

39:35.582 --> 39:37.618
You mean if you wanna stand me up
again?

39:39.127 --> 39:40.162
Lois, that was--

39:40.336 --> 39:42.918
A mistake. Agreed.
Why don't we just table this whole...

39:43.089 --> 39:46.798
...ofﬂce-thrown-together-in-the-trenches-
sparks thing, okay?

39:46.968 --> 39:49.584
Back to basics,
keep the game on the ﬁeld.

39:51.848 --> 39:53.804
Yeah, that's a good rule.

39:56.978 --> 39:59.264
You should add that to the list.

40:16.164 --> 40:17.370
Ready?

40:17.540 --> 40:19.451
Ready as you are.

40:20.794 --> 40:22.330
Chloe...

40:22.962 --> 40:26.125
...this will mean leaving your old life
as a reporter behind.

40:26.299 --> 40:28.711
You sure you wanna say goodbye
to that forever?

40:28.885 --> 40:31.797
Yesterday, I wouldn't have been
able to answer that question...

40:31.971 --> 40:35.589
...but after spending the day
at the Daily Planet, I realized...

40:36.142 --> 40:37.882
...that's someone else's life.

40:40.688 --> 40:43.179
Interesting.
Everyone seems to have so much clarity...

40:43.358 --> 40:46.020
...after a dose of the Zatanna dust.

40:46.194 --> 40:49.903
Almost makes me wish I had my turn
at the magic lamp too.

40:51.199 --> 40:53.690
I'll save you the heel blisters.

40:54.077 --> 40:56.033
You already know what you really want.

40:56.204 --> 40:57.740
We all do.

40:57.914 --> 40:59.700
We just don't listen.

41:01.876 --> 41:04.128
And you're sure this is it?

41:06.005 --> 41:08.212
This is where I belong.

41:14.848 --> 41:17.464
COMPUTER:
Aquaman online.

41:17.642 --> 41:19.598
Canary online.

41:19.769 --> 41:21.600
Cyborg online.

41:21.771 --> 41:23.978
Impulse online.

41:24.149 --> 41:25.855
Arrow online.

41:32.657 --> 41:35.865
Watchtower is ofﬁcially online.

41:38.079 --> 41:40.195
Let's get to work.

42:15.658 --> 42:17.649
[ENGLISH SDH]
